                      USENIX Winter 1993
             Technical Conference & Vendor Display

Wednesday & Thursday, January 27 & 28, 1993, 12 - 6 pm
Town & Country Hotel, San Diego, California

USENIX, the UNIX and Advanced Computing Systems Professional and
Technical Association, is hosting a Vendor Display during its Winter
1993 Technical Conference.  Approximately thirty providers of UNIX-
related and advanced computing products and services will have the
opportunity to meet with attendees in a relaxed atmosphere, conducive
to serious, productive discussion.

USENIX conference attendees really appreciate seeing vendors at our
small and informal displays because there is time to ask questions and
get to know the products.  USENIX conference-goers are eager to learn
about new products and services.  Most of all, they want to get a hands-
on look at the technology on display and enjoy productive meetings with
technically savvy vendor representatives, which is precisely what the
USENIX Winter 1993 Vendor Display will provide.

The vendor display is just down the hall from the main conference
sessions and display hours take advantage of scheduled session breaks.
To make your participation very easy, we provide a furnishings package
and identification sign.  Just carry in your product and literature,
set it out, and get ready to answer questions.  USENIX folks like to
keep it simple!

Over 2,000 attendees are expected at the Winter Conference in San Diego.
They are sophisticated, highly focused, mid to high-level technical
managers, who use, design, develop, and buy UNIX-related and advanced
computing products and services.  They are also the experts to whom
others turn before making purchases.

USENIX has been the premier technical and professional association for
operating systems and UNIX gurus for 19 years.  USENIX conferences are
widely recognized as the place to find out about UNIX-related technology
years before it's released.  Naturally, our conferences attract the most
sophisticated of UNIX technical professionals.

Cost of space

$1200 per 10' x 10' standard draped space, a 10' x 20' space is the
maximum that will be offered to any one vendor.

Supplied furnishings package

